properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 30 at 3:27PM AKST until January 31 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. The cold wind chills will
cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to exposed skin.
Expect wind chills up to 50 below zero.

* WHERE...In passes south of the Denali Park Entrance.

* WHEN...8 PM this evening to noon Friday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...In passes south of the Denali Park
Entrance, north winds gusting to 30 mph will increase later this
evening and continue through Friday morning creating wind
chills up to 50 below zero.
properties.instruction:
A Wind Chill Advisory means that cold air and sustained wind
speeds of 15 mph or more will create low wind chills. Frost bite
and hypothermia can occur if precautions are not taken.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO NOON AKST FRIDAY
